        "en": "Next week I start fifth grade. Since I've never been to a real school before, I am pretty much totally and completely petrified. People think I haven't gone to school because of the way I look, but it's not that. It's because of all the surgeries I've had. Twenty-seven since I was born. The bigger ones happened before I was even four years old, so I don't remember those. But I've had two or three surgeries every year since then (some big, some small), and because I'm little for my age, and I have some other medical mysteries that doctors never really figured out, I used to get sick a lot. That's why my parents decided it was better if I didn't go to school. I'm much stronger now, though. The last surgery I had was eight months ago, and I probably won't have to have any more for another couple of years.",
        "cn": "下周我就要上五年级了。因为我以前从未上过真正的学校，所以我差不多完全、彻底地吓呆了。人们认为我没去上学是因为我的长相，但不是那样的。这是因为我做过的所有手术。从我出生起就有二十七次了。大的那些手术在我还不到四岁时就发生了，所以我不记得那些。但从那以后我每年都要做两三次手术（有些大的，有些小的），而且因为我比同龄人小，还有一些医生一直没搞明白的医学谜团，我过去经常生病。那就是为什么我父母决定如果我不去上学可能会更好。不过，我现在强壮多了。我上一次手术是在八个月前，而且可能在未来几年内都不需要再做任何手术了。",
