        "en": "But she didn't come back that night. Dad did. He told me Auggie had had a bad first day and Mom was helping him through it. He asked me how my day had gone and I told him fine. He said he didn't believe me for a second, and I told him Miranda and Ella were acting like jerks. (I didn't mention how I took the subway home by myself, though.) He said nothing tests friendships like high school, and then proceeded to poke fun at the fact that I was reading War and Peace. Not real fun, of course, since I'd heard him brag to people that he had a \"fifteen-year-old who is reading Tolstoy.\" But he liked to rib me about where I was in the book, in a war part or in a peace part, and if there was anything in there about Napoleon's days as a hip-hop dancer. It was silly stuff, but Dad always managed to make everyone laugh. And sometimes that's all you need to feel better.",
        "cn": "但那天晚上她没有回来。爸爸来了。他告诉我奥吉的第一天过得很糟糕，妈妈正在帮他度过难关。他问我一天过得怎么样，我告诉他很好。他说他一秒钟都不相信，我就告诉他米兰达和埃拉表现得像个混蛋。（不过我没提我是怎么自己坐地铁回家的。）他说没有什么比高中更能考验友谊了，然后接着拿我正在读《战争与和平》这件事开玩笑。当然，不是真的取笑，因为我听过他向别人吹嘘他有一个“正在读托尔斯泰的十五岁女儿”。但他喜欢逗我，问我书读到哪里了，是战争部分还是和平部分，以及书里有没有关于拿破仑当嘻哈舞者的日子。都是些傻话，但爸爸总能让每个人都笑。而有时候，那就是让你感觉好起来所需要的全部。",
