        "id": 1,
        "en": "So in August my parents got this call from Mr. Tushman, the middle-school director. And my Mom said: \"Maybe he calls all the new students to welcome them,\" and my dad said: \"That's a lot of kids he'd be calling.\" So my mom called him back, and I could hear her talking to Mr. Tushman on the phone. This is exactly what she said: \"Oh, hi, Mr. Tushman. This is Amanda Will, returning your call? Pause. Oh, thank you! That's so nice of you to say. He is looking forward to it. Pause. Yes. Pause. Yeah. Pause. Oh. Sure. Long pause. Ohhh. Uh-huh. Pause. Well, that's so nice of you to say. Pause. Sure. Ohh. Wow. Ohhhh. Super long pause. I see, of course. I'm sure he will. Let me write it down . . . got it. I'll call you after I've had a chance to talk to him, okay? Pause. No, thank you for thinking of him. Bye bye!\"",
        "cn": "所以八月时，我父母接到了中学校长塔什曼先生的电话。我妈妈说：“也许他给所有新生打电话欢迎他们，” 我爸爸说：“那他要打的电话可真多。” 于是我妈妈给他回了电话，我能听到她在电话里和塔什曼先生说话。这正是她说的：“哦，嗨，塔什曼先生。我是阿曼达·威尔，回您的电话？（停顿）哦，谢谢您！您这么说真是太好了。他很期待。（停顿）是的。（停顿）嗯。（停顿）哦。当然。（长停顿）哦哦。嗯哼。（停顿）嗯，您这么说真是太好了。（停顿）当然。哦哦。哇。哦哦哦。（超长停顿）我明白了，当然。我肯定他会的。让我记下来……好了。我和他谈过之后会给您打电话，好吗？（停顿）不，谢谢您能想到他。再见！\"",
