        "id": 1,
        "en": "Despite what Tushman said, there was no \"clean slate\" when I went back to school in January. In fact, things were totally weird from the second I got to my locker in the morning. I'm next to Amos, who's always been a pretty straight-up kid, and I was like, \"Yo, what up?\" and he basically just nodded a half hello and closed his locker door and left. I was like, okay, that was bizarre. And then I said: \"Hey, what up?\" to Henry, who didn't even bother half-smiling but just looked away. Okay, so something's up. Dissed by two people in less than five minutes. Not that anyone's counting. I thought I'd try one more time, with Tristan, and boom, same thing. He actually looked nervous, like he was afraid of talking to me.",
        "cn": "尽管塔什曼先生那么说，但一月份我回到学校时，并没有什么“全新的开始”。事实上，从我早上到储物柜的那一秒起，事情就完全不对劲了。我旁边是阿莫斯，他一直是个挺爽快的孩子，我当时就说：“哟，你好吗？” 他基本上只是半点了个头算是打了招呼，就关上储物柜门走了。我心想，好吧，这太古怪了。然后我对亨利说：“嘿，你好吗？”，他甚至都懒得半笑一下，只是移开了目光。好吧，所以是出事了。不到五分钟就被两个人鄙视了。倒也不是说有人在数。我想我再试一次，和特里斯坦，然后砰的一声，同样的事情。他看起来其实很紧张，好像怕和我说话似的。",
