        "en": "The next day at lunch, stupid me, I sat down at a table with Tristan, Nino, and Pablo. I thought maybe they were safe because they weren't really considered popular, but they weren't out there playing D&D at recess, either. They were sort of in-betweeners. And, at first, I thought I scored because they were basically too nice to not acknowledge my presence when I walked over to the table. They all said \"Hey,\" though I could tell they looked at each other. But then the same thing happened that happened yesterday: our lunch table was called, they got their food, and then headed toward a new table on the other side of the cafeteria.",
        "cn": "第二天午餐时，愚蠢的我，和特里斯坦、尼诺、巴勃罗坐在一张桌子旁。我想也许他们是安全的，因为他们不怎么被认为是受欢迎的，但他们也不会在课间休息时去玩《龙与地下城》。他们算是中间派。而且，起初，我以为我得分了，因为当我走到桌边时，他们基本上都太好人了，不好意思不理会我的存在。他们都说了“嘿”，尽管我看得出他们互相看了看。但接着和昨天一样的事情发生了：我们的午餐桌被叫到了，他们拿了食物，然后就走向了餐厅另一边的一张新桌子。",
