        "id": 7,
        "en": "I've never seen Dad cry before, but I saw him cry tonight. I had gone into Mom and Dad's bedroom looking for Mom to put me to bed, but saw Dad sitting on the edge of the bed, taking off his socks. His back was to the door, so he didn't know I was there. At first I thought he was laughing because his shoulders were shaking, but then he put his palms on his eyes and I realized he was crying. It was the quietest crying I've ever heard. Like a whisper. I was going to go over to him, but then I thought maybe he was whisper-crying because he didn't want me or anyone else to hear him. So I walked out and went to Via's room, and I saw Mom lying next to Via on the bed, and Mom was whispering to Via, who was crying. So I went to my bed and put on my pajamas without anyone telling me to and put the night-light on and turned the light off and crawled into the little mountain of stuffed animals I had left on my bed earlier. It felt like that all had happened a million years ago. I took my hearing aids off and put them on the night table and pulled the covers up to my ears and imagined Daisy snuggling with me, her big wet tongue licking my face all over like it was her favorite face in the world. And that's how I fell asleep.",
        "cn": "我以前从未见过爸爸哭，但今晚我看到他哭了。我走进爸爸妈妈的卧室找妈妈给我盖被子，但看到爸爸坐在床边脱袜子。他背对着门，所以他不知道我在那里。起初我以为他在笑，因为他的肩膀在抖动，但接着他用手掌捂住了眼睛，我意识到他在哭。那是我听过的最安静的哭声。像一声耳语。我本打算走过去，但后来我想也许他是在无声地哭泣，因为他不想让我或任何其他人听到。于是我走了出去，去了维娅的房间，我看到妈妈躺在维娅旁边的床上，妈妈正在对哭泣的维娅低语。所以我回到我的床上，没等任何人告诉我，就穿上了睡衣，打开小夜灯，关掉大灯，然后爬进了我早些时候留在床上的那座毛绒玩具小山里。感觉所有那些事都像发生在一万亿年前一样。我摘下助听器，把它们放在床头柜上，把被子拉到耳朵上，想象着黛西依偎着我，她那湿漉漉的大舌头舔遍我的脸，好像那是她在世界上最喜欢的脸。我就是那样睡着的。",
