        "en": "We followed the crowd to the auditorium, where students handed out programs at the front entrance. We found seats in the fifth row, close to the middle. As soon as we sat down, Mom started looking inside her pocketbook. \"I can't believe I forgot my glasses!\" she said. Dad shook his head. Mom was always forgetting her glasses, or her keys, or something or other. She is flaky that way. \"You want to move closer?\" said Dad. Mom squinted at the stage. \"No, I can see okay.\" \"Speak now or forever hold your peace,\" said Dad. \"I'm fine,\" answered Mom.",
