        "en": "The bus driver started unloading our duffel bags, and I went to find mine while Mom talked to Mr. Tushman and Ms. Rubin, who had walked over to her. As I rolled my bag toward her, a lot of kids who don't usually say anything to me were nodding hello, or patting my back as I walked by them. \"Ready?\" Mom said when she saw me. She took my duffel bag, and I didn't even try to hold on to it: I was fine with her carrying it.",
