        "id": 3,
        "en": "Jack's version of the story was probably the best because he's so funny, but in whatever version of the story, and no matter who was telling it, two things always stayed the same: I got picked on because of my face and Jack defended me, and those guys—Amos, Henry, and Miles—protected me. And now that they'd protected me, I was different to them. It was like I was one of them. They all called me \"little dude\" now—even the jocks. These big dudes I barely even knew before would knuckle-punch me in the hallways now.",
